<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge,chrome=1">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Background Image Example</title>
    <meta name="author" content="">
    <meta name="description" content="">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <link rel="icon" href="favicon.ico">
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="apple-touch-icon.png">
    <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
    <%= action_cable_meta_tag %>
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag    'application', media: 'all', 'data-turbolinks-track' => 'reload' %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag 'application', 'data-turbolinks-track' => 'reload' %>
    <!-- HTML5 shim and Respond.js for IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->
    <!--[if lt IE 9]>
      <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js"></script>
      <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js"></script>
    <![endif]-->
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="header">Welcome to my sample application!</h1>
      <p class="lead">This application is merely an example of how you can integrate <a href"https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap-sass rel="nofollow"">Bootstrap 3</a> and <a href"https://github.com/FortAwesome/font-awesome-sass rel="nofollow"">Font Awesome</a> into a Ruby on Rails application using SASS. I also added a background image so that someone could see how to do so in CSS. The image file can be found in: app > assets > images and it comes from <a href"https://unsplash.com rel="nofollow"">unsplash.com</a> and the photo is by <a href"https://unsplash.com/photos/NKSGuJzExIo rel="nofollow"">Paul Itkin</a>.</p> 
      </div>
      <%= yield %>
    <hr>
    <footer>
      <p class="pull-right"><a href="#">Back to top</a></p>
      <p>&copy; 2016 My Company LLC.&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;
      <%= link_to 'Privacy Policy', page_path('privacy') %>&nbsp;&bull;&nbsp;
      <%= link_to 'Terms of Service', page_path('terms') %></p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
